Fettucine with Pistachio Pesto

1 c packed basil leaves
1/2 c packed spinach leaves
1/2 c shelled pistachios
1 large garlic clove (or 2 small)
juice of 1 lemon (~1 tbsp)
1/4 tsp salt
3 tbsp freshly grated parmesan cheese (use 1 tsp of mustard if vegan)
1/4-1/3 c olive oil
1/4 c heavy cream (optional)
1 lb bag of fresh fettucinie
parmesan for garnish
lemon zest and crushed pistachios for garnish

Cook the pasta according to package directions. Place all the pesto ingredients except the olive oil in a food processor. Process until the mixture is fine, then add the olive oil and process until the mixture is a smooth sauce. When the pasta is done, drain well. Then toss about 1/2 of the pesto with the pasta. If using cream, add with the pesto sauce to the cooked pasta. Serve the pasta drizzling ~1 tsp and sprinkle with parmesan cheese, lemon zest and crushed pistachios.


Nutrition:
calories: 313
total fat: 10.9g
saturated fat: 2.8g
cholesterol: 7.2mg
sodium: 296.6mg
total carbohydrate: 40.7g
dietary fiber: 4g
sugars: 2g
protein: 14.1g
